    <h2>Detailed Professional Experience</h2>
    <div class="details">
        <div class="job-description">
            <h3>My Journey in Cybersecurity and IAM</h3>
            <p>
                From humble beginnings in retail tech support, I discovered that security isn’t just about systems; it’s about safeguarding what matters most to people. 
                This human-centric philosophy has been the cornerstone of my career, shaping how I tackle challenges like implementing Zero Trust architectures 
                and pioneering decentralized identity solutions.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="job-description">
            <h3>Innovating Beyond Credentials</h3>
            <p>
                My expertise spans leading IAM solutions—CyberArk, SailPoint, AWS, and Azure—but what sets me apart is my ability to think beyond the conventional. 
                Inspired by sci-fi's visionary ideas, I craft forward-thinking security architectures that address not only today’s threats but also anticipate tomorrow’s challenges.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="job-description">
            <h3>Transforming Identity Management</h3>
            <p>
                Over 13+ years, I’ve seen identity management evolve from static, hierarchical models to fluid, decentralized frameworks. In one healthcare project, I spearheaded 
                the integration of W3C's Decentralized Identifiers (DIDs) alongside traditional authentication methods, creating a system that was both secure and accessible 
                for crisis-response medical staff.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="job-description">
            <h3>Strategic Adaptability in Action</h3>
            <p>
                My philosophy is rooted in embracing change. Across sectors like pharmaceuticals, retail, and federal contracting, I’ve transformed crises into opportunities. 
                For instance, by collaborating with an employee whose unauthorized automation script sparked innovation, I turned a compliance concern into a secure, enterprise-wide 
                process improvement.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="job-description">
            <h3>Security as an Organic System</h3>
            <p>
                In my own garden, I’ve created "security zones" akin to IAM principles—from public-facing spaces to highly restricted areas. This hands-on analogy not only simplifies 
                complex concepts for stakeholders but also reinforces my belief that security must be adaptable, dynamic, and human-centric.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="job-description">
            <h3>Looking to the Future</h3>
            <p>
                The rise of decentralized identity excites me. Whether deploying blockchain authentication or crafting user-centric access solutions, I dismantle outdated paradigms 
                while embracing emerging technologies. Corporate volatility energizes me, presenting opportunities to innovate security solutions that are resilient and forward-thinking.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="job-description">
            <h3>A Holistic Approach</h3>
            <p>
                Effective security should empower, not restrict. Beyond developing frameworks, I mentor emerging professionals and explore innovations like quantum computing’s implications 
                for cryptography. My philosophy intertwines permaculture’s principles with security architecture, creating systems that adapt and thrive.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="job-description">
            <h3>The Path Ahead</h3>
            <p>
                Committed to pushing the boundaries of IAM, I remain focused on delivering adaptable, people-first security solutions. By combining visionary strategies with practical 
                implementation, I help organizations navigate the complexities of the digital age while ensuring that security serves humanity—not the other way around.
            </p>
        </div>
